as with many meteor showers the visible rate is greatest in the pre - dawn hours , since more meteoroids are scooped up by the side of the earth moving forward into the stream , corresponding to local times between midnight and noon , as can be seen in the accompanying diagram.http://meteorshowersonline.com/what_is.html while many meteors arrive between dawn and noon , they are usually not visible due to daylight .

the solar system : examples of these celestial events include perseids , orionids & leonids

